WEBVTT

00:02.670 --> 00:03.037
[Birds chirping]

00:06.374 --> 00:09.710
[Utensil clinking]

00:10.711 --> 00:12.113
[Utensil clanks]

00:12.146 --> 00:15.649
[Microwave door opens, closes]

00:15.683 --> 00:17.451
[Microwave beeps, whirs]

00:17.485 --> 00:20.054
Hi.
Good morning.

00:20.088 --> 00:23.491
[Sighs]
I got it: "Catch the Comet."

00:23.524 --> 00:25.126
Oh.

00:25.159 --> 00:27.661
No. [Laughs]
Why not?

00:27.695 --> 00:30.298
Because it sounds
like the flu.

00:30.331 --> 00:31.732
[Liquid pouring]
Or the clap.

00:31.765 --> 00:34.335
How 'bout: "Let's Comet"?

00:34.368 --> 00:36.270
How 'bout, let's not.

00:36.304 --> 00:38.339
It's like Q-tip,
Kleenex, Band-Aid --

00:38.372 --> 00:40.608
We could be
the first Internet brand.

00:40.641 --> 00:42.676
Yes, and I would love
to be your focus group.

00:42.710 --> 00:44.278
Just after 10:00 a.m.

00:44.312 --> 00:47.381
But Rover's vulnerable,
one manager down...

00:47.415 --> 00:49.683
Joe.

00:49.717 --> 00:51.319
Come on.
That's a little evil.

00:51.352 --> 00:53.421
It's a joke.

00:53.454 --> 00:55.356
Relax.

00:55.389 --> 00:57.658
Hey, I-I want us
to visit him soon, okay?

00:57.691 --> 00:59.227
[Microwave beeping]
Mm-hmm.

00:59.260 --> 01:01.462
He knows I told you,
and he feels bad...

01:01.495 --> 01:02.763
I think
he wants to apologize.

01:02.796 --> 01:05.133
There's no need.
[Sighs]

01:05.166 --> 01:06.500
We still have
a better approach.

01:06.534 --> 01:08.136
And as it turns out,

01:08.169 --> 01:10.138
the "genius" behind
their new search algorithm

01:10.171 --> 01:12.206
is unavailable to them...

01:12.240 --> 01:13.774
Mm.

01:13.807 --> 01:16.210
Cheese egg?

01:17.311 --> 01:19.680
Wow. [Chuckles]

01:19.713 --> 01:23.484
"Search it, find it...
com-it."

01:23.517 --> 01:26.220
[Breathes deeply]

01:26.254 --> 01:28.489
It's perfect.

01:30.324 --> 01:33.494
Donna:
Thanks for coming in.

01:33.527 --> 01:36.830
I thought it was important
that we speak face to face --

01:36.864 --> 01:39.500
and in private.

01:39.533 --> 01:43.671
I wrote ninety percent
of the code Rover's built on.

01:43.704 --> 01:46.674
Yes, back when it was
a medical indexing company.

01:46.707 --> 01:48.542
But Rover's evolved,

01:48.576 --> 01:50.378
and you haven't evolved
with it.

01:50.411 --> 01:52.280
I've done everything
you've asked me to do.

01:52.313 --> 01:53.581
Why am I
the one that has to go?

01:53.614 --> 01:55.583
Bos has already stepped away.

01:55.616 --> 01:57.918
And frankly,
your deal is much more --

01:57.951 --> 02:00.221
I made this company
with my friends.

02:00.254 --> 02:03.324
Do you think I give a shit
about an exit package?!

02:03.357 --> 02:05.393
We were fine
until you came in

02:05.426 --> 02:07.728
and started demanding
the impossible.

02:07.761 --> 02:12.166
If I've been hard on you,
I'm sorry.

02:12.200 --> 02:13.534
[Breathes deeply]

02:13.567 --> 02:15.803
But this isn't
about what's fair.

02:15.836 --> 02:17.938
This is about survival.

02:17.971 --> 02:19.807
I don't think
you care about the money.

02:19.840 --> 02:22.676
But I do think you care
about your friends.

02:30.651 --> 02:32.420
[Sighs]

02:32.453 --> 02:35.756
The fact is, by passing someone
else's work off as your own,

02:35.789 --> 02:39.960
you've put them
in a precarious position.

02:39.993 --> 02:42.830
The only way to protect them

02:42.863 --> 02:45.499
is to take
the search algorithm apart

02:45.533 --> 02:49.403
and build Rover's own
proprietary version of it.

02:49.437 --> 02:53.507
And for that to work,
you can't be involved.

02:56.544 --> 03:01.849
I do know what it's like,
to feel like a failure.

03:01.882 --> 03:06.454
To feel like
you don't measure up.

03:06.487 --> 03:08.656
But if you don't step aside

03:08.689 --> 03:10.258
and let me bring in
someone else,

03:10.291 --> 03:13.827
you and your friends
could end up with nothing.

03:16.497 --> 03:21.302
[Breathes deeply]

03:21.335 --> 03:23.337
So what do I tell them?

03:23.371 --> 03:24.705
The truth.

03:24.738 --> 03:26.907
I'm burned out.

03:26.940 --> 03:30.311
I've been struggling
for awhile now.

03:30.344 --> 03:31.612
Rover's in a good place.

03:31.645 --> 03:36.250
I feel it's time
for me to move on...

03:36.284 --> 03:38.786
Try it.

03:38.819 --> 03:43.691
I'm burned out.

03:43.724 --> 03:46.494
It's been hard
for awhile now,

03:46.527 --> 03:48.929
and I think
it's time to move on...

03:48.962 --> 03:58.939
**

03:58.972 --> 04:04.912
**

04:04.945 --> 04:06.480
Now...?

04:06.514 --> 04:08.716
Take all the time you need.

04:08.749 --> 04:15.489
**

04:15.523 --> 04:17.558
[Door opens]

04:17.591 --> 04:19.059
**

04:19.092 --> 04:22.963
[Dialing]

04:22.996 --> 04:24.932
[Door closes]

04:24.965 --> 04:34.942
**

04:34.975 --> 04:44.952
**

04:44.985 --> 04:54.962
**

04:54.995 --> 05:00.834
**

05:01.902 --> 05:03.571
Haley!

05:03.604 --> 05:05.939
Get over here!

05:11.111 --> 05:12.480
What is it, Dad?

05:12.513 --> 05:14.047
Well, we have
something really important

05:14.081 --> 05:15.883
that we need to discuss.

05:15.916 --> 05:17.418
Okay.

05:17.451 --> 05:19.420
I think you know
what I'm talking about.

05:19.453 --> 05:21.989
No. Uh...

05:22.022 --> 05:24.358
Rockets!

05:24.392 --> 05:25.693
No. Way!

05:25.726 --> 05:27.127
Happy birthday, Bug.
Let's go this afternoon!

05:27.160 --> 05:28.962
Well, slow down.
We can't.

05:28.996 --> 05:30.864
We still have to recategorize
the site, and everyone's --

05:30.898 --> 05:32.900
But the weather's perfect,
visibility's awesome!

05:32.933 --> 05:35.736
Haley, come on.
And today's my actual birthday.

05:35.769 --> 05:38.005
Yeah, but if we go Saturday,
we can invite your friends.

05:38.038 --> 05:39.573
I'll ask them right now.

05:39.607 --> 05:40.974
No, your school friends,
okay?

05:41.008 --> 05:42.876
They have to work.
Besides, it's your birthday.

05:42.910 --> 05:44.545
It's not a national holiday.

05:44.578 --> 05:46.780
Okay, well,
what about inviting Katie?

05:46.814 --> 05:49.683
Really?

05:49.717 --> 05:53.454
Yeah, c'mon, let's do it.
Just us.

05:53.487 --> 05:57.558
Let me see
if I can reach Cam.

05:57.591 --> 05:59.727
I'll check to see
if she can move up the day.

05:59.760 --> 06:00.928
You're the best!
[Dial tone]

06:00.961 --> 06:04.164
It's not 100%!

06:04.197 --> 06:06.099
This is
just so unlike Cecil.

06:06.133 --> 06:08.001
Look, shake-ups
like this happen.

06:08.035 --> 06:10.771
As far as I'm concerned,
it's no refection on you

06:10.804 --> 06:12.840
or on the long-term viability
of Rover.

06:12.873 --> 06:14.608
But this will raise eyebrows,
won't it?

06:14.642 --> 06:15.943
I-I mean, for a cofounder

06:15.976 --> 06:17.711
to leave when the company's
doing so well --

06:17.745 --> 06:19.480
Trust me, the only thing
anyone cares about

06:19.513 --> 06:20.748
is how much traffic
we're getting.

06:20.781 --> 06:22.450
And in that respect,
Tanya's right.

06:22.483 --> 06:23.884
We're doing really well.

06:23.917 --> 06:26.654
And with the Series A,
we have the opportunity

06:26.687 --> 06:28.722
to attract
some formidable talent.

06:28.756 --> 06:31.191
I want you guys to focus
on optimizing the site.

06:31.224 --> 06:32.960
And I'll take lead
on hiring

06:32.993 --> 06:36.063
and make sure we land
the best CTO in the Valley.

06:36.096 --> 06:38.165
Is anyone good
even available?

06:38.198 --> 06:39.967
Yeah, Bobby Aron is.

06:40.000 --> 06:41.034
Bobby Aron?

06:41.068 --> 06:42.570
Mm-hmm.
Are you kidding?

06:42.603 --> 06:43.871
That guy's
a -- a legend.

06:43.904 --> 06:45.939
Microsoft's making
a huge play for him.

06:45.973 --> 06:47.007
I really don't think --

06:47.040 --> 06:48.208
Listen to me.

06:48.241 --> 06:50.578
We're the big ones.

06:50.611 --> 06:53.481
Any CTO would be lucky
to be with us.

06:53.514 --> 06:56.183
That's how we operate
from now on. Got it?

06:56.216 --> 06:58.218
All right.
Yep.

06:58.251 --> 06:59.687
Got it. [Sighs]

06:59.720 --> 07:02.222
Okay. [Sighs]

07:02.255 --> 07:05.526
[Laughs]

07:05.559 --> 07:08.061
Hey.
How's it look?

07:08.095 --> 07:10.598
Nice. El Gordo!

07:10.631 --> 07:12.500
[Chuckling] Yeah.

07:12.533 --> 07:14.502
You know what it means,
right?

07:14.535 --> 07:16.136
Yeah. "Handsome."

07:16.169 --> 07:18.872
Exactly.

07:18.906 --> 07:21.008
Hey, you see that?

07:21.041 --> 07:22.476
Uh-huh.

07:22.510 --> 07:23.811
Haley drew it.

07:23.844 --> 07:26.547
Sailors get one tattooed
for every 5,000 miles.

07:26.580 --> 07:27.781
But you know what she said?

07:27.815 --> 07:29.850
Since the rocket's 1/100th
in scale,

07:29.883 --> 07:31.752
it only needs
to cover fifty.

07:31.785 --> 07:33.487
Well, you haven't
launched yours yet, so...

07:33.521 --> 07:34.988
What, do you honestly think
I'm not gonna launch

07:35.022 --> 07:36.924
that thing 50 miles?

07:36.957 --> 07:38.892
Fair enough.

07:38.926 --> 07:41.895
[Laughter]

07:41.929 --> 07:43.196
Katie:
No, don't worry, hon.

07:43.230 --> 07:44.932
Do you think it's weird
that she didn't want

07:44.965 --> 07:46.600
to invite
any of her school friends?

07:46.634 --> 07:48.969
No.

07:49.002 --> 07:50.571
School friends
are overrated.

07:50.604 --> 07:52.139
Hmm.

07:52.172 --> 07:54.107
She seems really happy.

07:54.141 --> 07:55.843
And Katie is great.

07:55.876 --> 07:59.647
I feel like
it's missing something...

08:02.650 --> 08:04.117
Oh, you're planning
on going orbital?

08:04.151 --> 08:06.086
Definitely exosphere
on this one.

08:06.119 --> 08:07.521
Mm.

08:07.555 --> 08:09.089
You guys do this a lot?

08:09.122 --> 08:10.958
Yeah, we used to go
all the time

08:10.991 --> 08:12.726
until my mom
blew her hand off.

08:12.760 --> 08:16.029
It's just...
we didn't even see it coming.

08:16.063 --> 08:17.598
You know?
You are hilarious.

08:17.631 --> 08:19.032
[Laughs]

08:19.066 --> 08:21.034
...so then, after I practically
promised her a kidney,

08:21.068 --> 08:23.537
your neighbor makes
her poor son run ten miles...

08:23.571 --> 08:25.172
One. One mile.
...just to come
and knock on your door

08:25.205 --> 08:26.974
and give you a message?
So?

08:27.007 --> 08:29.176
It's not like I didn't give him
a ride home afterwards.

08:29.209 --> 08:31.745
Phones were invented
in the 19th century, you know,

08:31.779 --> 08:33.814
when America
was still mostly agrarian.
Mm-hmm.

08:33.847 --> 08:35.115
I mean,
you could build your own.

08:35.148 --> 08:36.884
In fact, you should.

08:36.917 --> 08:38.285
You're a lot of trouble

08:38.318 --> 08:40.721
when you've got too much time
on your hands.

08:42.055 --> 08:44.658
I told you,
I did that to help Bos.

08:44.692 --> 08:46.560
He asked me for help, too,

08:46.594 --> 08:48.629
but I didn't go out
and write him an algorithm.

08:48.662 --> 08:51.732
Okay,
well, don't worry,

08:51.765 --> 08:53.634
I'm done.

08:53.667 --> 08:56.604
I'm sick of tech.
The whole thing.

08:56.637 --> 08:59.072
What are you,
washed up at 32?

08:59.106 --> 09:01.775
Come on.
You got one lousy review.

09:01.809 --> 09:04.645
And do you have any idea what
people said bout the Symphonic?

09:04.678 --> 09:06.346
Come on, I know you.

09:06.379 --> 09:08.348
You dream in code.

09:08.381 --> 09:09.349
Yeah.

09:09.382 --> 09:12.152
Not anymore.

09:14.888 --> 09:16.356
-Hey, guys!
-Hey!

09:16.389 --> 09:18.058
-Guys, guys.
-We're ready!

09:18.091 --> 09:19.893
Come on.

09:19.927 --> 09:22.362
[Echo & the Bunnymen's
"Seven Seas" plays]

09:22.395 --> 09:26.233
**

09:26.266 --> 09:30.103
* Stab a sorry heart

09:30.137 --> 09:31.639
* With your favorite finger

09:31.672 --> 09:33.907
-All right, get your keys in.
-Key's in.

09:33.941 --> 09:35.909
Hey, hey. Would you --
Would you film me?
* Paint the whole world blue

09:35.943 --> 09:37.878
[Laughs]

09:37.911 --> 09:41.048
* And stop your tears
from stinging *
Happy birthday, Bug.

09:41.081 --> 09:42.916
* Hear the cavemen singing

09:42.950 --> 09:45.285
And T-minus five...

09:45.318 --> 09:46.654
* Good news they're bringing
All: Four...

09:46.687 --> 09:49.156
three, two, one...

09:49.189 --> 09:52.693
* Seven seas
Blast off!

09:52.726 --> 09:53.861
* Swimming them so well
Boom.

09:53.894 --> 09:56.664
[Laughter]

09:56.697 --> 09:59.667
* Glad to see

09:59.700 --> 10:01.735
* My face among them

10:01.769 --> 10:03.270
* Kissing the tortoise

10:03.303 --> 10:06.807
* Seven seas

10:06.840 --> 10:09.242
* Swimming them so well
[Laughs]

10:09.276 --> 10:11.044
Haley: Where'd it go?
* Glad to see

10:11.078 --> 10:12.379
[Laughter]
Where is it?!

10:12.412 --> 10:13.914
I'm supposed to stop it!

10:13.947 --> 10:15.916
* My face among them
[Laughs]

10:15.949 --> 10:19.753
* Kissing the tortoise shell

10:19.787 --> 10:21.254
[Cowboy Junkies' "Sweet Jane"
plays in background]

10:21.288 --> 10:25.258
**

10:25.292 --> 10:26.894
[Door opens, closes]

10:26.927 --> 10:28.428
* Anyone who's ever had
a heart *

10:28.461 --> 10:30.831
What is this,
music to kill yourself by?

10:30.864 --> 10:33.100
Hey, would you mind
bringing me a beer?

10:33.133 --> 10:35.435
You can have one too,
if you want.

10:35.468 --> 10:37.871
Don't tell your dad.
[Bottle cap clinks]

10:37.905 --> 10:40.040
* And anyone
who's ever played the part *

10:40.073 --> 10:41.842
So how's Bos?

10:41.875 --> 10:43.343
Good, I think.

10:43.376 --> 10:46.279
* Wouldn't turn around
and hate it *

10:46.313 --> 10:49.717
And how's your first sip
of beer?

10:49.750 --> 10:51.919
* Sweet Jane

10:51.952 --> 10:53.320
It's awful.

10:53.353 --> 10:56.189
But he's good, right?
They released him yesterday?

10:56.223 --> 10:58.125
How do you know?

10:58.158 --> 11:00.127
I saw him Friday,
after school.

11:00.160 --> 11:01.428
I thought visiting hours
at the hospital

11:01.461 --> 11:02.830
were in the morning.

11:02.863 --> 11:04.331
I told them
I was his granddaughter.

11:04.364 --> 11:07.300
[Laughs]

11:07.334 --> 11:09.102
I love that about you.

11:09.136 --> 11:11.238
You know that, right?

11:11.271 --> 11:15.776
You're absolutely fearless.

11:15.809 --> 11:17.177
It's a hospital.

11:17.210 --> 11:19.112
They're not gonna arrest me.

11:19.146 --> 11:21.248
Well, I don't know
where you get it.

11:21.281 --> 11:23.116
You never got
in any trouble?

11:23.150 --> 11:26.186
Do anything crazy?

11:26.219 --> 11:30.223
I was pretty cautious...

11:30.257 --> 11:31.792
C'mon.

11:31.825 --> 11:34.094
**

11:34.127 --> 11:35.495
C'mon.

11:35.528 --> 11:36.964
[Laughs]

11:36.997 --> 11:39.800
Well...

11:39.833 --> 11:41.902
your dad and I used to go
camping all the time,

11:41.935 --> 11:44.071
and we went
to this one campsite.

11:44.104 --> 11:47.007
And the locals always talked
about this quarry they'd go to.

11:47.040 --> 11:48.776
It was a swimming hole.

11:48.809 --> 11:51.378
So your dad and I drove out
there, and we found it.

11:51.411 --> 11:52.479
It was incredible.

11:52.512 --> 11:54.281
It was this cliff

11:54.314 --> 11:57.484
overlooking the glassiest,
clearest blue water

11:57.517 --> 11:59.486
you've ever seen.

11:59.519 --> 12:01.488
And your dad
wouldn't jump in.

12:01.521 --> 12:03.290
[Chuckles]
He wouldn't.
It was too high.

12:03.323 --> 12:04.925
So I laughed at him,

12:04.958 --> 12:06.827
and he said,
"I bet you won't, either."

12:06.860 --> 12:09.362
So before I could think twice,
I ran right up to the edge,

12:09.396 --> 12:11.531
did a cartwheel right off.

12:11.564 --> 12:13.533
Holy shit, Mom,

12:13.566 --> 12:17.037
it's a miracle
that I was even born.
[Chuckles]

12:17.070 --> 12:19.439
I guess
I just didn't believe

12:19.472 --> 12:21.408
that I could really get hurt,
you know?

12:21.441 --> 12:25.378
It just felt...free.

12:25.412 --> 12:27.180
You have that,

12:27.214 --> 12:30.517
and I don't ever want you
to lose it.

12:30.550 --> 12:34.321
Don't ever stop yourself
'cause you're scared...

12:34.354 --> 12:36.857
Okay.

12:36.890 --> 12:39.059
**

12:39.092 --> 12:42.863
Well, next time I get
in trouble, remember:

12:42.896 --> 12:44.064
It's 'cause
I'm being "brave."

12:44.097 --> 12:45.899
[Laughs]

12:45.933 --> 12:47.500
All right.

12:47.534 --> 12:50.337
I got to do my homework,
so...

12:50.370 --> 12:51.805
[Sighs]

12:51.839 --> 12:53.473
All right.

12:53.506 --> 12:56.243
G'night.

12:56.276 --> 12:57.878
G'night.

12:57.911 --> 13:01.815
* Seem to whisper to me

13:01.849 --> 13:03.984
* When you smile

13:04.017 --> 13:06.419
**

13:06.453 --> 13:11.892
* La-la-la-la, la-la-la

13:11.925 --> 13:17.564
* La-la-la, la-la-la

13:17.597 --> 13:23.203
* La-la-la-la, la-la-la

13:23.236 --> 13:28.408
* La-la-la, la-la-la

13:32.145 --> 13:32.779
Joe:
It's amazing, isn't it?

13:35.148 --> 13:36.549
One minute, Haley's four

13:36.583 --> 13:38.585
and building a fort
out of the sofa cushions.

13:38.618 --> 13:40.988
The next minute, she's...
Haley:
I'm crushing your head.

13:41.021 --> 13:43.123
...telling
"Kids in the Hall" jokes.

13:44.624 --> 13:48.228
It's just...so cool.
[water running]

13:48.261 --> 13:51.164
Oh, yeah,
kids are great --

13:51.198 --> 13:54.301
if you can give birth
to a fourteen-year-old.

13:54.334 --> 13:57.137
I will see you tonight.

13:57.170 --> 13:58.538
Bye.

14:04.344 --> 14:08.548
[Door opens, closes]

14:18.591 --> 14:21.028
[Mouse clicking]

14:21.061 --> 14:23.063
[Keyboard clacking]

14:26.233 --> 14:29.336
[Breathes deeply]

14:32.639 --> 14:34.374
[Mouse clicking]

14:40.413 --> 14:42.149
[Keyboard clacks]

14:45.352 --> 14:49.056
What the hell...?

14:49.089 --> 14:51.658
[Mouse clicks]

14:51.691 --> 14:59.499
**

