15:09.342 --> 15:11.244
[Mouse clicking]

15:11.278 --> 15:17.650
**

15:17.684 --> 15:19.019
[Mouse clicks]

15:19.052 --> 15:21.388
**

15:21.421 --> 15:23.156
[Mouse clicks]

15:23.190 --> 15:24.524
**

15:24.557 --> 15:25.692
[Mouse clicks]

15:25.725 --> 15:27.227
[Gasps]

15:27.260 --> 15:29.096
[Mouse clicks]

15:29.129 --> 15:33.666
**

15:33.700 --> 15:35.135
[Mouse clicks]

15:35.168 --> 15:42.275
**

15:42.309 --> 15:45.979
Joe: All right,
just relax.

15:46.013 --> 15:47.547
Clear your mind.

15:47.580 --> 15:50.750
Woman: Is anyone else having
problems with the monitor?

15:50.783 --> 15:53.553
[Laughs]

15:53.586 --> 15:56.456
Coward.

15:56.489 --> 15:58.391
[Sighs]

15:58.425 --> 16:02.029
Okay, uh, the first thing
that I think of

16:02.062 --> 16:05.032
when I hear "Internet" is...

16:05.065 --> 16:06.266
A computer?

16:06.299 --> 16:08.301
A computer.

16:08.335 --> 16:10.237
-And porn.
-Porn.

16:10.270 --> 16:12.605
-Porn?
-Lots of porn.

16:12.639 --> 16:15.642
I put in a request to be on
the team that catalogues porn.

16:15.675 --> 16:17.210
Beep, beep, beep...

16:17.244 --> 16:19.146
[Imitates modem static]

16:19.179 --> 16:21.214
[Sighs]

16:21.248 --> 16:23.483
[Ball bouncing]

16:29.689 --> 16:31.124
[Ringing]

16:31.158 --> 16:32.192
Gordon:
Gordon Clark.

16:32.225 --> 16:33.426
Hey, it's me.

16:33.460 --> 16:34.494
I'm sorry
this is so last second,

16:34.527 --> 16:36.029
but can we reschedule dinner?

16:36.063 --> 16:37.230
Yeah, no problem.

16:37.264 --> 16:39.666
N-Nothing to report anyway.

16:39.699 --> 16:42.635
Well, actually, there is.

16:42.669 --> 16:44.604
Uh, I got a phone call

16:44.637 --> 16:46.539
from Haley's
guidance counselor.

16:46.573 --> 16:49.142
She's flunking history
and bio.

16:49.176 --> 16:50.543
Our Haley?

16:50.577 --> 16:52.479
Yeah, she hasn't turned in
some assignments,

16:52.512 --> 16:55.448
and apparently she bombed
the last couple tests...

16:55.482 --> 16:58.585
I don't get it,
she was doing so great...

16:58.618 --> 17:01.521
Well, maybe she's just
trying to do too much.

17:01.554 --> 17:03.790
Come on, Donna.
She loves Comet.

17:03.823 --> 17:06.659
I know she loves it,
but I think she needs a break.

17:06.693 --> 17:09.462
I'm afraid she's putting work
above everything else.

17:09.496 --> 17:12.199
Hmm. Well, I wonder
where she gets that from.

17:12.232 --> 17:15.468
Excuse me. I always put
the girls before work.

17:15.502 --> 17:17.170
And if you need me
to talk to Haley

17:17.204 --> 17:18.538
because you can't handle it,
then --

17:18.571 --> 17:20.373
I-I --
I'm sorry, all right?

17:20.407 --> 17:21.641
I just...

17:21.674 --> 17:23.443
I don't want to be
the bad guy here.

17:23.476 --> 17:24.577
And I do?

17:24.611 --> 17:26.479
Okay, I'll talk to her.

17:26.513 --> 17:28.581
Thank you, Gordon.

17:28.615 --> 17:30.350
[Sighs]

17:30.383 --> 17:32.319
[Telephone clicks in cradle]

17:39.459 --> 17:42.462
**

17:42.495 --> 17:43.630
Whassup?

17:43.663 --> 17:45.698
Haley: [Laughs]

17:45.732 --> 17:47.134
Uh, it's a nice place.

17:47.167 --> 17:49.402
It's...charming.

17:49.436 --> 17:52.305
Yeah, thanks for stopping.
I was staved.

17:52.339 --> 17:55.642
So...favorite site?

17:55.675 --> 17:57.610
Um...

17:57.644 --> 18:00.680
God, I can't pick just one --
That's too hard!

18:00.713 --> 18:03.483
Uh, what did
everyone else say?

18:03.516 --> 18:05.418
Well,
one person's favorite site

18:05.452 --> 18:06.719
was a purple screen.

18:06.753 --> 18:08.555
Just that --
a purple screen.

18:08.588 --> 18:10.423
Melissa, right?
Mm-hmm.

18:10.457 --> 18:11.791
[Chuckles]
She's obsessed.

18:11.824 --> 18:13.260
And someone else
recommended

18:13.293 --> 18:15.195
"Strawberry Pop Tart
Blowtorches."

18:15.228 --> 18:16.663
Oh, yeah,
Arnie found that one!

18:16.696 --> 18:19.432
We spent an entire day
setting Pop-Tarts on fire.

18:19.466 --> 18:22.135
I think we destroyed
like three toasters.

18:22.169 --> 18:24.871
[Chuckles]
That's impressive.

18:24.904 --> 18:26.639
But I'm not sure
how any of these

18:26.673 --> 18:28.741
are gonna get
the average person online.

18:28.775 --> 18:30.510
Why not?
They got me online.

18:30.543 --> 18:33.313
How so?

18:33.346 --> 18:35.315
Well, when I first looked
at the Internet --

18:35.348 --> 18:37.217
remember your Post-its? --

18:37.250 --> 18:38.618
I thought
it was pretty boring.

18:38.651 --> 18:41.621
It was nothing
but databases and archives...

18:41.654 --> 18:43.790
But then I found
all this other stuff --

18:43.823 --> 18:45.858
like this kid, Justin,
who's writing about his life.

18:45.892 --> 18:47.360
And this other girl

18:47.394 --> 18:49.329
who was obsessed
with "I Love Lucy"...

18:49.362 --> 18:51.364
And what about that
was so appealing?

18:51.398 --> 18:52.799
I don't know.

18:52.832 --> 18:55.435
Um, school was not good.

18:55.468 --> 18:57.804
I mean, no one was torturing me
or anything like that,

18:57.837 --> 19:00.540
but it's just, like,
everyone's always pretending,

19:00.573 --> 19:02.309
you know?
Mm.

19:02.342 --> 19:05.345
That's why the Web's so great,
'cause no one pretends.

19:05.378 --> 19:07.780
You just put it out there,
who you really are.

19:07.814 --> 19:09.782
And if people respond to it,
that's great.

19:09.816 --> 19:11.718
But if not, who cares?

19:11.751 --> 19:13.253
At least they saw you

19:13.286 --> 19:16.189
and not just some projection,
you know?

19:16.223 --> 19:18.458
Yeah.

19:18.491 --> 19:19.459
Vanessa: Hey.

19:19.492 --> 19:21.228
Hey.

19:21.261 --> 19:22.895
You guys working?

19:22.929 --> 19:24.397
Uh, yeah.
Hi, Vanessa.

19:24.431 --> 19:26.699
Um, this is my boss,
Joe MacMillan.

19:26.733 --> 19:28.501
Actually, cofounder.

19:28.535 --> 19:30.237
Cool. [Chuckles]

19:30.270 --> 19:31.604
[Chuckles]

19:31.638 --> 19:33.773
I'm totally addicted to IUMA,
by the way.

19:33.806 --> 19:35.642
Their indie rock section's,
like, incredible --

19:35.675 --> 19:37.777
I know.
It's like who needs Sub Pop?

19:37.810 --> 19:39.546
Did you find
that Julep compilation?

19:39.579 --> 19:40.747
The one
with the Bratmobile song?

19:40.780 --> 19:41.848
Yes!

19:41.881 --> 19:43.616
"Let's talk about...

19:43.650 --> 19:45.352
dogs."
Dogs.

19:45.385 --> 19:46.753
* Dun-na-na-na-na-na
* Da-da-da, da-da-da

19:46.786 --> 19:48.388
Yeah.
-Yeah.

19:48.421 --> 19:50.523
The Heavens to Betsy song's,
like, hella cool, too.

19:50.557 --> 19:53.460
Yeah.

19:53.493 --> 19:56.329
[Bell dinging]

19:56.363 --> 19:59.499
I better get back to work,
but I'll see you later.

19:59.532 --> 20:00.667
Yeah. For sure.

20:00.700 --> 20:01.701
Cool.

20:01.734 --> 20:03.836
**

20:03.870 --> 20:06.806
[Breathes deeply]

20:06.839 --> 20:09.909
Woman on P.A.: Order 35, this is
your two deluxe combos ready.

20:09.942 --> 20:11.711
**

20:11.744 --> 20:15.415
She seems cool.

20:15.448 --> 20:18.618
Uh, what were
we talking about again?

20:18.651 --> 20:21.854
So on the Internet...

20:21.888 --> 20:26.326
you think you can be
who you really are?

20:26.359 --> 20:29.329
With Rover we cannot only
count the number of users,

20:29.362 --> 20:32.499
we can track what they click on,
how long they look at it --

20:32.532 --> 20:34.534
I mean,
it's an advertiser's dream.

20:34.567 --> 20:35.602
So, it is about selling.

20:35.635 --> 20:36.736
No, it's [Sighs]

20:36.769 --> 20:40.039
It's about change.

20:40.072 --> 20:42.041
At Rover,
you could be part

20:42.074 --> 20:45.345
of a universal,
decentralized platform

20:45.378 --> 20:47.447
that's already
changing the world.

20:47.480 --> 20:49.282
Look.
You could join Microsoft

20:49.316 --> 20:52.385
and let them tell you
what the future will be.

20:52.419 --> 20:55.622
Or you could join us
and tell them.

20:55.655 --> 20:57.890
**

20:57.924 --> 21:00.427
[Sighs]

21:00.460 --> 21:03.763
I accepted the Microsoft offer
this morning.

21:03.796 --> 21:06.399
I only kept this meeting
because, well, growing up,

21:06.433 --> 21:08.067
I was a huge fan
of Mutiny --

21:08.100 --> 21:09.336
really Community.

21:09.369 --> 21:11.304
I-I made friends,

21:11.338 --> 21:12.805
and I traded bootlegs

21:12.839 --> 21:15.508
and bought
and sold computer parts.

21:15.542 --> 21:17.810
It was a lifesaver, really.

21:17.844 --> 21:19.412
And I, uh...

21:19.446 --> 21:21.948
**

21:21.981 --> 21:25.084
Well, I guess
I just wanted to thank you.

21:25.117 --> 21:29.722
That's really nice to hear,
but I [Sighs]

21:29.756 --> 21:31.591
I was really hoping
this would work out.

21:31.624 --> 21:32.659
[Chuckles]

21:32.692 --> 21:34.461
[Sighs]

21:34.494 --> 21:35.962
Can I ask you a question?

21:35.995 --> 21:38.565
**

21:38.598 --> 21:42.935
Community was so far ahead
of its time.

21:42.969 --> 21:45.605
Why haven't you tried
to re-create it?

21:45.638 --> 21:50.109
**

21:50.142 --> 21:52.945
Mutiny was
the most fun I ever had.

21:52.979 --> 21:54.881
We didn't know
what we were doing.

21:54.914 --> 21:56.649
It was one crisis
after another.

21:56.683 --> 22:00.553
Hm.
But it worked.

22:00.587 --> 22:05.525
The failure of that was...

22:05.558 --> 22:07.960
Well, what's that saying --

22:07.994 --> 22:11.030
You grow stronger
at the broken places...?

22:11.063 --> 22:14.100
Hm.
Anyway.

22:14.133 --> 22:15.802
Yeah, the truth is,

22:15.835 --> 22:19.806
I am trying to build
another version of Community.

22:19.839 --> 22:21.941
Except, this time,
it's the entire Internet.

22:21.974 --> 22:24.577
It's everyone.

22:24.611 --> 22:26.446
That's what's so exciting
about Rover.

22:26.479 --> 22:31.818
It's flying without a net
into the great unknown.

22:31.851 --> 22:33.786
Huh.
It's terrifying,

22:33.820 --> 22:36.789
and it's exhilarating.

22:36.823 --> 22:38.691
[Sighs]

22:38.725 --> 22:40.026
Well...

22:40.059 --> 22:43.796
I have been known
to change my mind, though.

22:43.830 --> 22:46.165
Yeah.

22:46.198 --> 22:47.600
Microsoft's safe.

22:47.634 --> 22:49.769
But, um,
well, what's that saying?

22:49.802 --> 22:52.605
No risk, no reward, right?

22:52.639 --> 22:53.840
I'm in.

22:53.873 --> 22:56.809
If you still want me,
that is.

22:56.843 --> 22:58.811
I-I -- Y-- Absolutely!

22:58.845 --> 23:00.146
Okay, okay.
[Laughs]

23:00.179 --> 23:01.981
[Gasps]

23:02.014 --> 23:04.584
I might need your shark side
to help me out, though.

23:04.617 --> 23:06.819
The Beast of Redmond
ain't gonna like this one bit.
Oh.

23:06.853 --> 23:08.621
They don't scare me.

23:08.655 --> 23:10.056
Yeah,
I can't imagine who would.

23:10.089 --> 23:11.958
[Chuckles]

23:11.991 --> 23:12.959
To risk.

23:12.992 --> 23:16.463
[Sighs, chuckles]

23:16.496 --> 23:18.130
**

23:18.164 --> 23:21.634
Ahh!

23:21.668 --> 23:23.670
Hey.
You up for one more?

23:32.445 --> 23:32.945
[Dog barking in distance]

23:38.785 --> 23:41.053
[Sighs]

23:51.531 --> 23:54.066
[Groans, clears throat]

23:54.100 --> 23:56.669
Ah.

24:02.274 --> 24:03.510
Hey.

24:03.543 --> 24:05.478
Hello.
[Clears throat]

24:05.512 --> 24:06.813
Feeling okay...?

24:06.846 --> 24:08.815
Yeah.

24:08.848 --> 24:11.618
Uh, there's coffee...

24:11.651 --> 24:15.755
I should, uh --
I should get going.

24:18.057 --> 24:21.027
Yeah, we should, um...

24:21.060 --> 24:22.762
We should talk
about the job --

24:22.795 --> 24:24.631
You know...

24:24.664 --> 24:27.767
it's fine.

24:27.800 --> 24:29.602
Yeah.

24:29.636 --> 24:31.103
O-Okay.

24:33.806 --> 24:35.808
[Sighs]

24:35.842 --> 24:38.745
["Jump Right Out
of This Jukebox" plays]

24:38.778 --> 24:42.549
**

24:42.582 --> 24:44.517
* Suppose that
I should come to life *

24:44.551 --> 24:45.785
[Knock on door]
John?

24:45.818 --> 24:47.854
* When they play this song

24:47.887 --> 24:50.189
* I could be in a lot of places
at once *

24:50.222 --> 24:51.891
It's from Sam.

24:51.924 --> 24:54.193
Oh.

24:54.226 --> 24:57.063
[Chuckles]

24:57.096 --> 24:58.264
Aww.

24:58.297 --> 24:59.932
That's me with all the hair.

24:59.966 --> 25:02.569
[Both laugh]

25:02.602 --> 25:04.637
**

25:04.671 --> 25:07.206
What a kid.

25:07.239 --> 25:09.809
John,
this whole experience...

25:09.842 --> 25:13.112
it's been making me think.

25:13.145 --> 25:15.582
At the hospital,
it was so hard.

25:15.615 --> 25:17.149
I had no say
in your care

25:17.183 --> 25:18.317
and if something
had gone wrong...

25:18.350 --> 25:20.119
Yeah, but it didn't.

25:20.152 --> 25:21.654
I'm fine...

25:21.688 --> 25:23.990
Well, it's not just that.

25:24.023 --> 25:25.658
[Sighs]

25:25.692 --> 25:29.929
At the restaurant,
there was a moment...

25:29.962 --> 25:33.065
the way you looked.

25:33.099 --> 25:34.601
I thought
I was losing you.

25:34.634 --> 25:35.902
Oh.

25:35.935 --> 25:39.138
I love you.

25:39.171 --> 25:42.775
And I don't know how much time
together we have left.

25:42.809 --> 25:45.745
So what're we waiting for?

25:45.778 --> 25:49.882
Now, I don't have a ring --

25:49.916 --> 25:51.984
And I know
you're expecting a big rock...

25:52.018 --> 25:55.354
Goddamn, woman,
what're you doing to my heart?

25:55.387 --> 25:58.157
So...?

25:58.190 --> 26:03.262
**

26:03.295 --> 26:07.967
Do you remember the
Patterson housing development?

26:08.000 --> 26:10.169
You passed on it.

26:10.202 --> 26:12.304
I thought
it was worth a second look.

26:12.338 --> 26:15.875
**

26:15.908 --> 26:17.109
How much?

26:17.143 --> 26:18.978
300k.

26:19.011 --> 26:21.748
I wanted to take care of it
myself.

26:21.781 --> 26:25.117
I didn't want you to know
what a fool I was --

26:25.151 --> 26:27.286
I thought workin' at Rover
would be a win-win,

26:27.319 --> 26:32.692
and then we started hitting
a wall, and I panicked.

26:32.725 --> 26:36.162
You saw the site.
It wasn't good enough.

26:36.195 --> 26:38.731
We couldn't get over
that hump.

26:38.765 --> 26:44.070
So I-I got Cam to help build
the search engine.

26:44.103 --> 26:46.072
And Donna found out,

26:46.105 --> 26:48.841
and then at restaurant,
she knew that she --

26:48.875 --> 26:50.409
I'm sorry.

26:50.442 --> 26:52.945
Diane.

26:52.979 --> 26:54.981
**

26:55.014 --> 26:57.784
Diane!

26:57.817 --> 27:01.120
[Indistinct conversations]

27:01.153 --> 27:02.421
**

27:02.454 --> 27:07.159
[Breathes deeply]

27:07.193 --> 27:09.862
**

27:09.896 --> 27:13.866
Haley? C'mere.

27:18.270 --> 27:22.241
What is it? Pete's waiting
to take me back to school.

27:22.274 --> 27:25.978
We need to talk
about your grades.

27:26.012 --> 27:28.948
Okay...

27:28.981 --> 27:30.717
The school called.

27:30.750 --> 27:33.119
They said that
you're failing two classes.
Failing?

27:33.152 --> 27:36.288
I -- Maybe I missed a few tests,
but I can just retake them.

27:36.322 --> 27:37.957
Well...
I'll talk to my teacher.
I can...

27:37.990 --> 27:40.192
We agreed
that you could work here

27:40.226 --> 27:42.161
if you kept up your grades.

27:42.194 --> 27:44.330
That was the deal.

27:44.363 --> 27:46.933
S-So what're you saying?
I have to stop working?

27:46.966 --> 27:49.168
Just temporarily until you can
bring your grades back up,

27:49.201 --> 27:50.469
and then we can talk --

27:50.502 --> 27:52.238
But, Dad --
It's Haley's Comet!

27:52.271 --> 27:54.173
You wouldn't even have
a company if weren't for me!

27:54.206 --> 27:55.842
Hey, listen.
Calm down, Bug.

27:55.875 --> 27:57.910
That's not entirely accurate.
Stop calling me "Bug"!

27:57.944 --> 27:59.145
And why do
I even need school?

27:59.178 --> 28:00.379
I already have a job.

28:00.412 --> 28:02.481
Because you need school
to learn

28:02.514 --> 28:04.917
and to make friends --
My friends are here --

28:04.951 --> 28:07.754
And you can't fire me,
they need me!

28:07.787 --> 28:10.757
[Chuckling] Okay, well, I think
we'd be able to manage --

28:10.790 --> 28:13.392
Hey!

28:13.425 --> 28:17.429
Haley, clean it up.

28:17.463 --> 28:20.399
No.
Haley, if you ever want
to work here again,

28:20.432 --> 28:22.301
you will clean. It. Up.

28:23.836 --> 28:25.371
Haley!
[Door opens]

28:28.274 --> 28:31.143
[Indistinct conversations]
Ha-- Hey!

28:31.177 --> 28:33.245
Get back here!

28:33.279 --> 28:36.382
Haley!

28:36.415 --> 28:38.417
[Conversations stop]

28:38.450 --> 28:39.986
[Door closes]
What?!

28:40.019 --> 28:42.054
[Conversations resume]

28:47.827 --> 28:49.395
[Sighs]

28:49.428 --> 28:53.900
[Breathes deeply]

28:53.933 --> 28:55.367
Yes,
it's a red leather wallet.

28:55.401 --> 28:57.770
I was siting at the bar...

28:57.804 --> 28:58.871
You do?

28:58.905 --> 29:00.339
[Knock on door]

29:00.372 --> 29:03.075
I-I will come by tonight.
Thank you.

29:03.109 --> 29:05.177
[Telephone clicks in cradle,
door closes]

29:05.211 --> 29:06.412
Do you have a moment?

29:06.445 --> 29:08.047
What's going on...?

29:08.080 --> 29:11.317
[Sighs]

29:11.350 --> 29:13.252
I had a talk with John.

29:13.285 --> 29:16.889
And apparently
he's made some bad decisions

29:16.923 --> 29:18.124
regarding Rover.

29:18.157 --> 29:20.827
But I think
you already know that.

29:20.860 --> 29:23.495
Well, I [Sighs]

29:23.529 --> 29:25.131
I had my suspicions,

29:25.164 --> 29:28.567
but I didn't know for sure
until I saw Cam...

29:28.600 --> 29:30.502
It's done.

29:30.536 --> 29:31.938
Now, the important thing

29:31.971 --> 29:34.173
is to clean up the mess
and move on.

29:34.206 --> 29:37.176
I couldn't agree more.
Cecil is gone.

29:37.209 --> 29:38.444
We plan to find someone

29:38.477 --> 29:39.912
who can reverse engineer
Rover's code --

29:39.946 --> 29:41.247
Reverse engineer?
Why?

29:41.280 --> 29:43.282
Oh, to protect the site
from any liabilities --

29:43.315 --> 29:45.551
But if Cameron
built this code,

29:45.584 --> 29:47.253
the next step --
the only step --

29:47.286 --> 29:48.855
is to get her
to sign a release.

29:48.888 --> 29:49.989
That's how we protect
the site.

29:50.022 --> 29:52.391
Yes, yes.
[Sighs]

29:52.424 --> 29:54.393
But in this one case,

29:54.426 --> 29:57.329
I really think
that is the wrong move.

29:57.363 --> 29:59.231
I mean, why let Cameron know

29:59.265 --> 30:01.200
how valuable
what she gave us was?

30:01.233 --> 30:03.035
I mean, better
to just create our own version

30:03.069 --> 30:05.037
of the algorithm,
and no one will be any wiser.

30:05.071 --> 30:07.039
That doesn't make any sense.

30:07.073 --> 30:08.274
Look, there is
one simple solution,

30:08.307 --> 30:09.909
and it should've happened
immediately:

30:09.942 --> 30:11.610
pay Cameron whatever she wants
and be done with it.

30:11.643 --> 30:13.913
No!
I can't. I can't.

30:13.946 --> 30:16.082
I-I just...

30:16.115 --> 30:18.050
I-I can't.

30:18.084 --> 30:21.520
[Sighs]

30:30.029 --> 30:32.298
Well, this is
what's gonna happen.

30:32.331 --> 30:33.866
You're going
to go to Cameron

30:33.900 --> 30:35.434
and get her
to sign a release.

30:35.467 --> 30:37.603
And then
you will step away.

30:37.636 --> 30:39.939
And Trip will take over.

30:39.972 --> 30:42.875
Th-- I...

30:42.909 --> 30:44.643
That's not fair.

30:44.676 --> 30:46.378
He'll just --
He'll -- You know him.

30:46.412 --> 30:48.314
He'll use it!
To become managing partner?

30:48.347 --> 30:49.348
Perhaps.

30:49.381 --> 30:51.017
Maybe that's best.

30:51.050 --> 30:53.485
Frankly, you have
bigger issues to deal with.

30:53.519 --> 30:54.887
Get yourself together,
Donna.

30:54.921 --> 30:56.088
I'm tired
of holding your hand.

30:56.122 --> 30:57.489
None of this
would've happened

30:57.523 --> 31:00.159
if Bos felt like he could
just come and talk to you.

31:07.399 --> 31:10.536
[Door opens]
[Breathes sharply]

31:10.569 --> 31:12.471
[Door closes]

31:15.307 --> 31:18.110
[Sighs]

31:18.144 --> 31:19.311
I was surprised
to get your e-mail.

31:19.345 --> 31:21.547
I was about
to give up on you.

31:21.580 --> 31:23.950
Yeah. Um...

31:23.983 --> 31:26.452
So what is this about,
exactly?

31:26.485 --> 31:27.954
You, um...

31:27.987 --> 31:29.922
Did Atari send you or --
Oh, no.

31:29.956 --> 31:31.190
Although
they were kind enough

31:31.223 --> 31:32.959
to give me
a copy of "Pilgrim."

31:32.992 --> 31:36.195
They did?
You can get anything
if you know how to ask.

31:36.228 --> 31:38.130
I thought the game
was interesting --

31:38.164 --> 31:40.399
flawed, but interesting.

31:40.432 --> 31:41.633
I mean,
I've never played a game

31:41.667 --> 31:44.336
that actively blocks
your way so much.

31:44.370 --> 31:46.305
Yeah.

31:46.338 --> 31:51.010
Well, I, uh -- I was trying
to respect the gamer.

31:51.043 --> 31:52.979
Engage them,

31:53.012 --> 31:55.547
not treat them like
a passive receptacle, but --
Respect, sure,

31:55.581 --> 31:58.484
but you clearly didn't want
anyone to solve the game.

31:58.517 --> 32:00.987
Why, I have no idea.
That's your thing.

32:01.020 --> 32:05.057
But the world that you created
to contain the puzzles,

32:05.091 --> 32:07.626
that was interesting.

32:07.659 --> 32:10.129
And the graphics
were incredible.

32:10.162 --> 32:13.265
I'm sure they still
don't even come close

32:13.299 --> 32:14.633
to what you saw
in your head.

32:14.666 --> 32:16.368
Well, the computer for that
doesn't exist yet.

32:16.402 --> 32:18.070
You sure?

32:18.104 --> 32:20.339
Processor speed is growing
at an exponential rate.

32:20.372 --> 32:22.608
I've seen what's happening,
and it's mind-blowing.

32:22.641 --> 32:24.243
'Cause here's the thing:

32:24.276 --> 32:27.013
I don't think
you're a game designer.
Oh.

32:27.046 --> 32:29.148
I think
you're a world builder.

32:29.181 --> 32:31.350
**

32:31.383 --> 32:34.420
And I'd like
to work with you.

32:34.453 --> 32:37.023
I want to see
what you do next.

32:37.056 --> 32:39.725
* You're gonna wake up

32:39.758 --> 32:42.394
Okay.

32:42.428 --> 32:44.630
And why should
I want to work with you?

32:44.663 --> 32:46.165
Because here's
what I'm offering:

32:46.198 --> 32:50.236
no VCs.
No interference.

32:50.269 --> 32:52.204
What you said at MISC
was spot on:

32:52.238 --> 32:53.672
The model is broken.

32:53.705 --> 32:55.207
Parasitic.

32:55.241 --> 32:57.743
So I plan
to stay out of your way.

32:57.776 --> 33:01.013
While I do what, exactly?

33:01.047 --> 33:03.649
Whatever you want.

33:03.682 --> 33:06.185
**

33:06.218 --> 33:08.254
[Indistinct conversations]

33:08.287 --> 33:10.789
You okay?

33:10.822 --> 33:12.191
Yup.

33:12.224 --> 33:14.560
You wanna talk?
Nope.

33:14.593 --> 33:17.263
Hound Dogz.

33:17.296 --> 33:20.066
We were just there
yesterday.

33:20.099 --> 33:21.800
Yep.
She loves that place.

33:21.833 --> 33:24.703
No idea why,
the food sucks.

33:24.736 --> 33:26.772
Maybe it's not about
the food.

33:26.805 --> 33:30.076
[Sighs]

33:30.109 --> 33:33.045
When's she coming back?

33:33.079 --> 33:36.215
No idea.
She no longer works here.

33:36.248 --> 33:38.217
What did you do,
fire her?

33:38.250 --> 33:41.120
I gave her a choice,
and she walked.

33:41.153 --> 33:43.122
So get her back.

33:43.155 --> 33:44.690
Joe, she's flunking
her classes

33:44.723 --> 33:46.825
and copping
some major attitude.

33:46.858 --> 33:50.262
You don't understand,
Haley needs this place.

33:50.296 --> 33:52.764
She's not like other kids.

33:52.798 --> 33:56.435
She's got different, um...

33:56.468 --> 33:57.703
interests.

33:57.736 --> 34:00.772
Well, good for her.

34:00.806 --> 34:03.109
[Sighs]

34:03.142 --> 34:05.444
She's a little like me.

34:05.477 --> 34:07.146
When I was a kid,

34:07.179 --> 34:09.848
I would've given anything
for a place like this,

34:09.881 --> 34:13.452
someplace I could feel
like I belonged.

34:13.485 --> 34:16.722
Yeah? Well,
this is what parenting is.

34:16.755 --> 34:21.193
Setting limits, being
consistent, and discipline.

34:21.227 --> 34:22.528
You sound like my dad.

34:22.561 --> 34:24.696
Don't even start
to compare me to your father

34:24.730 --> 34:26.765
because the two of us are
not even in the same universe.

34:26.798 --> 34:32.238
All I'm saying is [Sighs]
he never really saw me.

34:32.271 --> 34:34.440
He just wanted me
to be like him.

34:34.473 --> 34:38.377
All I'm saying is that I see
Haley just fine.

34:38.410 --> 34:40.379
Okay, I may not sit around
sipping milkshakes with her,

34:40.412 --> 34:42.248
but I know
exactly who my daughter is.

34:42.281 --> 34:43.682
Are you sure about that?

34:43.715 --> 34:46.152
All right, what the hell
is that supposed to mean?

34:46.185 --> 34:48.420
Nothing.

34:48.454 --> 34:49.888
I just want
what's best for Haley.

34:49.921 --> 34:51.657
Oh, come on, Joe.

34:51.690 --> 34:53.192
You don't give a shit
about her

34:53.225 --> 34:54.726
beyond what she can do
for this company.

34:54.760 --> 34:57.429
You just want
what's best for you.

34:57.463 --> 35:01.567
That's why you're not a parent
and you never will be.

35:01.600 --> 35:04.236
[Sighs]

35:04.270 --> 35:06.738
[Water splashing]

35:11.477 --> 35:12.878
You're right.

35:24.190 --> 35:26.558
[Door closes]

35:30.462 --> 35:33.699
**

35:37.903 --> 35:39.438
[Glass clinks]

35:39.471 --> 35:40.939
[Door opens]

35:40.972 --> 35:42.574
Joanie:
Whoa, what level is that?

35:42.608 --> 35:43.675
[Door closes]

35:43.709 --> 35:46.778
Hey, guys.
How was school?

35:46.812 --> 35:50.416
She had a fight with Dad.

35:50.449 --> 35:52.851
What're you doing home
so early?

35:52.884 --> 35:55.287
Uh,
I wasn't feeling well.

35:55.321 --> 35:57.856
Oh.

35:57.889 --> 36:00.492
Cutting work.
Nice.

36:00.526 --> 36:01.893
We had a cool sub today.

36:01.927 --> 36:03.862
-Oh, yeah?
-She's American,

36:03.895 --> 36:06.265
but she went to college
in France.

36:06.298 --> 36:07.899
Apparently, you can do,
like, some, like,

36:07.933 --> 36:09.335
international-student thing,

36:09.368 --> 36:10.736
and she said
it's, like, it was amazing

36:10.769 --> 36:13.239
and that she saw these films
at the Cinémathèque,

36:13.272 --> 36:14.840
and that, um, they have
all these, like,

36:14.873 --> 36:17.709
really cool programs for, like,
film and photography, and --

36:17.743 --> 36:20.512
Do you know what I love
about you, Joanie?

36:20.546 --> 36:25.784
You are so...fearless.

36:27.286 --> 36:28.987
You know?

36:29.020 --> 36:30.322
Mm-hmm.

36:30.356 --> 36:32.724
I hope you never lose that.

36:32.758 --> 36:37.596
Just don't ever say no to
something because you're scared.

36:39.465 --> 36:40.799
[Chuckles]

36:40.832 --> 36:42.634
You want to
come play with me?

36:42.668 --> 36:44.903
Come on.
I'll show you all my secrets.

36:44.936 --> 36:47.706
It's okay.

36:47.739 --> 36:50.309
I'm gonna, um...

36:50.342 --> 36:52.711
I'm gonna go check with Haley
and see what she's up to.

36:52.744 --> 36:54.813
-Uh, okay.
-Yeah.

36:54.846 --> 37:00.686
**

37:00.719 --> 37:06.592
**

37:06.625 --> 37:07.859
[Glass clinks, mouse clicks]

37:07.893 --> 37:12.398
Where do you want to go?

37:23.074 --> 37:25.544
[Telephone rings]

37:25.577 --> 37:26.712
[Telephone beeps]

37:26.745 --> 37:28.380
Hello?

37:28.414 --> 37:30.982
Oh, Joe. Hey.

37:31.016 --> 37:32.918
Hey, it's Bos.

37:32.951 --> 37:34.486
Is Cameron there?

37:34.520 --> 37:37.789
Uh, no.

37:37.823 --> 37:39.858
Sorry.
You want to leave a message?

37:39.891 --> 37:41.860
No, no.
I'll just...

37:41.893 --> 37:44.262
I'll just call back later.

37:48.700 --> 37:50.769
Hey.

37:51.803 --> 37:53.972
How're you holding up?

37:54.005 --> 37:55.807
[Sighs]

37:55.841 --> 37:59.511
Well...

37:59.545 --> 38:00.712
[Bottle hisses]

38:00.746 --> 38:02.614
[Bottle cap clinks]

38:02.648 --> 38:05.451
[Sighs] What a mess.

38:10.522 --> 38:12.991
Well, I told myself
it was pride --

38:13.024 --> 38:14.926
just stupid pride.

38:14.960 --> 38:17.062
But the truth is...

38:17.095 --> 38:19.865
I wanted to know
I still mattered,

38:19.898 --> 38:22.468
wanted to know
I could shake things up.

38:22.501 --> 38:24.836
Mission accomplished.

38:24.870 --> 38:26.004
They is shook.

38:26.037 --> 38:27.673
Yeah.

38:27.706 --> 38:29.775
Well, I wouldn't know
anything about that.

38:29.808 --> 38:32.578
[Chuckles]

38:32.611 --> 38:36.014
You know, the things
that I've done...

38:36.047 --> 38:37.916
[Exhales sharply]

38:40.018 --> 38:42.421
I don't even know
why I did them.

38:42.454 --> 38:46.558
I just wanted everything,

38:46.592 --> 38:49.461
and I didn't care what

38:49.495 --> 38:52.063
or who I had to go through
to get it.

38:52.097 --> 38:54.900
Yeah.

38:54.933 --> 38:56.368
That guy.

38:56.402 --> 38:57.603
He was a real asshole.

38:57.636 --> 38:59.137
I think I hired him once.

38:59.170 --> 39:01.440
[Chuckles]
-Maybe I'm still that guy,

39:01.473 --> 39:03.108
and everybody can see it
but me.

39:03.141 --> 39:07.145
No. Recognizing you're
an asshole is half the battle.

39:07.178 --> 39:09.648
But I've seen how honest
you've been with Cam.

39:09.681 --> 39:14.520
That's a different man
than the one I first met, Joe.

39:14.553 --> 39:17.155
I could've used
some of that myself.

39:17.188 --> 39:18.890
Oh, we've got
our no-go zones.

39:18.924 --> 39:22.461
Well, sure, you lie and say
you love the ballet or whatever.

39:22.494 --> 39:24.896
Or maybe one of you
wants kids,

39:24.930 --> 39:26.031
the other one doesn't

39:26.064 --> 39:28.400
so you just
keep it to yourself.

39:29.835 --> 39:31.970
Cam wants kids?

39:32.003 --> 39:34.440
Mnh-mnh.

39:34.473 --> 39:39.445
Well,
maybe she'll surprise you.

39:39.478 --> 39:43.549
[Vehicle approaching]

39:43.582 --> 39:45.484
She might surprise you,
too.

39:45.517 --> 39:46.818
[Bottle clanks]

39:46.852 --> 39:47.919
Good luck.

39:47.953 --> 39:50.489
Wait.
[Groans]

39:50.522 --> 39:51.957
[Garage door opens]

39:51.990 --> 39:54.893
If you need a place to stay,
you're always welcome.

39:58.597 --> 39:59.931
["We Belong" plays on radio]

39:59.965 --> 40:03.201
* Maybe it's a sign
of weakness *

40:03.234 --> 40:06.805
* When I don't know
what to say *

40:06.838 --> 40:09.508
* Maybe I just wouldn't know

40:09.541 --> 40:13.479
* What to do with
my strength anyway *
* ...to do with
my strength anyway *

40:13.512 --> 40:17.483
* Have we become a habit?

40:17.516 --> 40:20.919
* Do we distort the facts?

40:20.952 --> 40:24.690
* Now, there's no
looking forward *
* No looking forward

40:24.723 --> 40:27.058
* Now, there's no turning back
* Now, there's no turning back

40:27.092 --> 40:29.961
* When you say
we belong to the light *
* Belong to the light

40:29.995 --> 40:33.198
* We belong to the thunder
* We belong to the thunder

40:33.231 --> 40:37.703
* We belong to
the sound of the words *
* Belong to the sound
of the words *

40:37.736 --> 40:41.072
* We've both fallen under
* We've both fallen under

40:41.106 --> 40:44.710
* Whatever we deny or embrace
* Whatever we deny or embrace

40:44.743 --> 40:47.513
* For worse or for better
* For worse or for better

40:47.546 --> 40:51.617
* We belong, we belong
* We belong, we belong

40:51.650 --> 40:54.753
* We belong together
* We belong together

40:54.786 --> 40:56.688
* We belong

40:56.722 --> 40:58.557
* We belong to the light
* We belong to the light

40:58.590 --> 41:01.627
[Siren chirps]
* We belong to the thunder

41:01.660 --> 41:05.664
* We belong to
the sound of the words *

41:05.697 --> 41:08.734
* We've both fallen under

41:08.767 --> 41:12.904
* Whatever we deny or embrace

41:12.938 --> 41:15.641
* For worse or for better

41:15.674 --> 41:18.276
* We belong --

41:18.309 --> 41:20.178
[Song stops, keys jostle,
car beeps]

41:22.113 --> 41:25.016
[Indistinct chatter]

41:25.050 --> 41:27.586
[Crickets chirping]

42:19.204 --> 42:23.575
So...what happened?

42:23.609 --> 42:25.143
I had two glasses of wine.

42:25.176 --> 42:27.613
That cop obviously needed
to fill his quota --

42:27.646 --> 42:29.114
our tax dollars at work.

42:29.147 --> 42:31.650
But, I mean, um,

42:31.683 --> 42:34.152
you've never even
gotten a ticket before.

42:34.185 --> 42:37.723
Yeah, well, now I have.

42:37.756 --> 42:42.828
[Laughs]

42:42.861 --> 42:46.865
What?

42:46.898 --> 42:50.235
Ah.

42:50.268 --> 42:54.673
I was just picturing
my 22-year-old self

42:54.706 --> 42:59.110
walking into AGGEK,

42:59.144 --> 43:02.013
lugging the Symphonic.

43:02.047 --> 43:05.617
Sit sits down, she pitches...

43:05.651 --> 43:08.119
and I crush her.

43:08.153 --> 43:09.821
[Chuckles]

43:09.855 --> 43:12.891
The young me
doesn't stand a chance.

43:12.924 --> 43:15.994
Oh, please.

43:17.162 --> 43:20.732
That 22-year-old was hardly
sweet and innocent.

43:20.766 --> 43:24.770
And the present you
isn't so ruthless.

43:24.803 --> 43:29.074
And they're all you,
all the versions.

43:29.107 --> 43:32.077
You're the same person
that you always were.

43:32.110 --> 43:36.414
And...

43:36.447 --> 43:38.817
I love that person.

43:38.850 --> 43:41.386
[Sniffs]

43:44.289 --> 43:47.292
[Crying]

44:05.176 --> 44:07.345
[Keys jingle, car beeps]

44:07.378 --> 44:10.749
[Engine starts]

44:13.685 --> 44:18.023
**

44:22.260 --> 44:25.230
[Birds chirping]

44:25.263 --> 44:35.240
**

44:35.273 --> 44:44.182
**

44:44.215 --> 44:45.784
[Keys rattle]

44:45.817 --> 44:54.359
**

44:54.392 --> 44:57.763
[Parking brake clicks,
engine shuts off]

44:57.796 --> 44:59.430
[Car door opens, closes]

44:59.464 --> 45:01.366
Hi.

45:01.399 --> 45:06.037
[Birds chirping]

45:06.071 --> 45:07.906
Thanks
for letting me come by.

45:07.939 --> 45:09.875
Sure.

45:09.908 --> 45:14.312
Sit down?

45:14.345 --> 45:17.182
[Exhales]

45:22.387 --> 45:24.890
[Taps table]

45:24.923 --> 45:27.525
Obviously,
we will compensate you.

45:27.558 --> 45:29.260
I thought we could start --

45:29.294 --> 45:31.830
No need.
[Cameron writes]

45:31.863 --> 45:33.832
No payment necessary.

45:33.865 --> 45:36.301
[Writing]

45:37.936 --> 45:40.071
[Paper rustles]

45:45.210 --> 45:48.013
Okay.

45:48.046 --> 45:50.048
Well, thank you.

45:52.483 --> 45:55.020
Don't worry.
I won't tell Joe.

45:56.454 --> 45:58.056
He already knows.
[Chuckles lightly]

45:59.825 --> 46:03.361
[Sighs]

46:05.096 --> 46:07.933
[Breathes deeply]

46:07.966 --> 46:09.968
Hey.

46:12.337 --> 46:14.272
You okay?

46:17.843 --> 46:19.911
[Horn honks]

46:19.945 --> 46:22.948
[Birds chirping]

46:29.154 --> 46:31.289
Thank you for this.

46:31.322 --> 46:33.925
I won't
bother you again.

46:33.959 --> 46:36.962
[Van approaching]

46:48.206 --> 46:51.609
Hey, Pete, slow down.

46:51.642 --> 46:54.212
I want to make a quick stop.

47:00.018 --> 47:01.987
[Engine shuts off,
keys jingle]

47:02.020 --> 47:04.122
[Rock music playing in distance]

47:04.155 --> 47:14.132
**

47:14.165 --> 47:19.137
["I Found the Star" playing
on radio]
* I've not done anything at all
since I last saw you *

47:19.170 --> 47:20.906
**

47:20.939 --> 47:25.210
* And I haven't had a thing
to eat for a day or two *

47:25.243 --> 47:27.578
Vanessa: Welcome to Hound Dogz,
can I help you?

47:27.612 --> 47:30.048
Yeah, let me get a, uh...

47:30.081 --> 47:33.218
a breakfast burrito
and a small coffee.

47:33.251 --> 47:36.054
Yeah, that'll be $2.80.
[Register beeps]

47:36.087 --> 47:38.924
[Tray clatters]

47:38.957 --> 47:40.658
Could I get a burrito
and a small coffee?

47:40.691 --> 47:44.595
Man: Coming right up.
[Register opens, printer whirs]

47:44.629 --> 47:47.265
**

47:47.298 --> 47:50.368
[Register closes]

47:50.401 --> 47:52.370
[Birds chirping]

47:52.403 --> 48:02.380
**

48:02.413 --> 48:12.390
**

48:12.423 --> 48:16.394
**

48:16.427 --> 48:21.299
[Keyboard clacking]

48:21.332 --> 48:25.470
[Modem dials]

48:25.503 --> 48:28.473
[Modem beeping]

48:28.506 --> 48:38.483
**

48:38.516 --> 48:40.018
[Beeps continue]

48:40.051 --> 48:50.028
**

48:50.061 --> 48:55.533
**

48:59.437 --> 49:05.310
**

49:09.380 --> 49:19.357
**

